Galaxy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="_6m7"&gt;A newfound giant black hole nearly as massive as 7 billion suns is dozens of times larger than astronomers expected given its host galaxy&#039;s Flying Stamp to Pluto&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="_6m7"&gt;They are three words that, after next week, will never be used to describe Pluto again, and they are about to witness their own up-close images of the dwarf planet Pluto.
